      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: bound JSON response reads to prevent OOM in update-check, minimax oauth, and docs search",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThree unbounded `response.json()` calls can buffer arbitrarily large HTTP responses into memory:\n\n1. **NPM registry** (`src/infra/update-check.ts`) — `openclaw/latest` metadata includes all versions, can be very large\n2. **MiniMax OAuth authorization** (`extensions/minimax/oauth.ts`) — success path unbounded while error path already uses `readResponseTextLimited`\n3. **Docs search** (`src/commands/docs.ts`) — search API response unbounded\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nEach fix follows the established bounded-reader pattern used in recent OOM fixes (#97706, #97808, #98191):\n- Use `readResponseWithLimit` / `readProviderJsonResponse` with explicit byte caps\n- Add oversized-response rejection tests\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Oversized NPM registry, MiniMax OAuth, and docs search responses are now cancelled mid-stream\n- Error messages change slightly for oversized responses\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Test Results\n```\nsrc/infra/update-check.test.ts — 20 passed (1 new oversized test)\nextensions/minimax/oauth.test.ts — 13 passed (1 new oversized test)\nsrc/commands/docs.test.ts — 4 passed (1 new oversized test)\n```\n\n### Files Changed\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/infra/update-check.ts` | `readResponseWithLimit` (4 MiB) for NPM registry |\n| `extensions/minimax/oauth.ts` | `readProviderJsonResponse` (16 MiB) for authorization |\n| `src/commands/docs.ts` | `readResponseWithLimit` (8 MiB) for docs search |\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
